# 🔹 1. Linux File Permissions

## Change File Permissions

```bash
chmod 755 deploy.sh
chmod 644 config.txt
chmod -R 750 /secure-data
```

## Permission Breakdown

| Permission | Meaning |
|------------|----------|
| 755 | Owner can read/write/execute, others can read/execute |
| 644 | Owner can read/write, others can only read |
| 750 | Secure access for owner and group only |

---

# 🔹 2. Ownership Management

## Change Ownership

```bash
chown dev1:projectteam app.log
chown -R deployuser:deployuser /deployments
```

## Verify Ownership

```bash
ls -l
```

---

# 🔹 3. File Operations

## Copy Files

```bash
cp app.conf backup.conf
```

## Move/Rename Files

```bash
mv old.log archived.log
```

## Remove Files & Directories

```bash
rm -rf temp/
```

## Search Files

```bash
find /projects -name "*.log"
```

---

# 🔹 4. Firewall Security

## Enable Firewall

```bash
sudo ufw enable
```

## Allow SSH & HTTP

```bash
sudo ufw allow 22
sudo ufw allow 80
```

## Check Firewall Status

```bash
sudo ufw status
```

---

# 🔹 5. SELinux Basics

## Check SELinux Status

```bash
getenforce
sestatus
```

## Disable SELinux Temporarily

```bash
sudo setenforce 0
```

## Enable SELinux Again

```bash
sudo setenforce 1
```

---

# 🔹 6. Timezone Management

## Check Current Timezone

```bash
timedatectl
```

## Set Timezone

```bash
sudo timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Kolkata
```

## Verify Timezone

```bash
timedatectl
```

---

# 🔹 7. Process Limits

## Check Current Limits

```bash
ulimit -a
```

## Increase Open File Limit

```bash
ulimit -n 4096
```

