# 🔹 8. Real-world Security Practices

## Monitor Failed Login Attempts

```bash
lastb
faillog
```

## Check Active Users

```bash
who
w
```

## View System Users

```bash
cat /etc/passwd
```

---

# 🔹 9. Secure SSH Configuration

## Edit SSH Config

```bash
sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
```

## Recommended Settings

```bash
PermitRootLogin no
PasswordAuthentication yes
```

## Restart SSH Service

```bash
sudo systemctl restart ssh
```

---

# 🔹 10. Check Open Ports

## View Listening Ports

```bash
ss -tulnp
```

## Alternative Command

```bash
netstat -tulnp
```

